column5: Hopefully this isn't posted twice....I apparently wasn't signed in on the first try. To keep it short...there is a real time webcam at a Vermilion Bay area resort. I've watched it for over a year....lots of fun watching the comings and goings of fisher people---the weather, the waves, the fish being brought in. Now, the dock appears to be empty...I've yet to see any guests and the dock looks very lonely.

Sitting in the MPLS airport currently and itâ€™s like being in a movie . . . Literally nobody around. Very strange! Been going every year since 83. Hope to reschedule for the fall to Country Cabins outside of Sioux lookout
There's a real good web cam of the Mississippi headwatershttps://www.dnr.state.mn.us/state_pa...eadwaters.html

That's the one I was referring to.... For those considering Minnesota as a back up, https://www.elyminnesota.com/live-webcams/ cams for a couple of area lakes (this is Boundary Waters area if you haven't heard of Ely....we named our cat after it)
Yeah Manotak's is on Perrault lake...
